## Exercise 1:

Here's an example of how you can achieve the desired layout using React Native and Expo:

```javascript
import React from 'react';
import { View, Text, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';

const Exercise1 = () => {
  return (
    <View style={styles.container}>
      <Text style={styles.header}>Here are my boxes</Text>
      <View style={styles.boxContainer}>
        <Rectangle color="#2aa198" name="Cyan: #2aa198" />
        <Rectangle color="#268bd2" name="Blue: #268bd2" />
        <Rectangle color="#d33682" name="Magenta: #d33682" />
        <Rectangle color="#cb4b16" name="Orange: #cb4b16" />
      </View>
    </View>
  );
};

const Rectangle = ({ color, name }) => {
  return (
    <View style={[styles.rectangle, { backgroundColor: color }]}>
      <Text style={styles.rectangleText}>{name}</Text>
    </View>
  );
};

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    flex: 1,
    padding: 16,
    alignItems: 'center',
  },
  header: {
    fontSize: 24,
    fontWeight: 'bold',
    marginBottom: 16,
  },
  boxContainer: {
    justifyContent: 'center',
  },
  rectangle: {
    width: 200,
    height: 50,
    marginBottom: 8,
    justifyContent: 'center',
    alignItems: 'center',
  },
  rectangleText: {
    color: 'white',
    fontWeight: 'bold',
  },
});

export default Exercise1;
```

You can use the `Exercise1` component in your main app file to display the header and rectangles with their respective colors and names.

## Exercise 2:

Here's an example of how you can create three centered squares with unique background colors using shared styles:

```javascript
import React from 'react';
import { View, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';

const Exercise2 = () => {
  return (
    <View style={styles.container}>
      <View style={[styles.square, styles.square1]} />
      <View style={[styles.square, styles.square2]} />
      <View style={[styles.square, styles.square3]} />
    </View>
  );
};

const sharedStyles = StyleSheet.create({
  square: {
    width: 100,
    height: 100,
    margin: 8,
  },
});

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    flex: 1,
    alignItems: 'center',
    justifyContent: 'center',
  },
  square1: {
    backgroundColor: 'red',
  },
  square2: {
    backgroundColor: 'green',
  },
  square3: {
    backgroundColor: 'blue',
  },
});

export default Exercise2;
```

You can use the `Exercise2` component in your main app file to display the three centered squares with their respective colors.

